George Woodrouffe Harris (6 August 1880 – 10 July 1954) was an English first-class cricketer. A right-handed batsman, he represented Hampshire in one first-class match in 1899 against Surrey. Harris made ten runs in Hampshire's first innings, but in the second innings Harris was bowled for a duck.
Harris died in Chorleywood, Hertfordshire on 10 July 1954.
